comments: Green (GSW) and Paschall (GSW) are each moving forward as marginal body contact occurs with Sabonis (IND) after Sabonis picks up his dribble.
Sabonis (IND) establishes his right foot as his pivot after picking up his dribble. He lifts and re-plants his pivot foot without releasing the ball.
Turner (IND) intentionally kicks the ball.
Curry (GSW) firms up in his screening position in Turner's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
Curry (GSW) and Holiday (IND) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Curry's (GSW) right arm is extended outward and marginal contact occurs with Sabonis' (IND) front as Sabonis goes over the pick.
Green's (GSW) left arm is extended outward as contact occurs with Brogdon's (IND) right arm and Green collapses his arm upon impact as he absorbs the contact.
Paschall (GSW) firms up in his screening position in Holiday's (IND) path and absorbs the contact.
Paschall (GSW) gathers the ball on his left foot as he receives the pass and takes two steps before attempting the dunk.
McDermott's (IND) left arm is extended outward as marginal contact occurs with Paschall's (GSW) right arm after his gather.
Paschall (GSW) moves laterally into Brogdon (IND) and initiates body contact after Brogdon's gather.
Sabonis' (IND) left hand is extended forward as marginal contact occurs with Curry's (GSW) arm/front. Sabonis then makes clean contact with the ball as Curry is passing.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Oubre Jr.'s (GSW) path following the hand-off and absorbs the contact.
Paschall (GSW) legally contests McDermott's (IND) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Turner (IND) rests his hands on Green's (GSW) back and marginal contact occurs as Turner releases away.
Turner (IND) and Brogdon (IND) make incidental contact with Green (GSW) as he retrieves the rebound.
Sabonis (IND) intentionally kicks the ball.
Brogdon (IND) commits a take foul on Green (GSW).
Curry (GSW) and Sabonis (IND) engage and disengage with one another as the screen is set.
Replay review of the foul called on Curry (GSW) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Curry delivers contact to McConnell (IND) that dislodges him from position in the corner.

Wiggins (GSW) brings his left arm up to contest the driving shot attempt and some contact occurs with the back of Brogdon's (IND) head. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Sabonis (IND) commits a take foul on Curry (GSW).
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Curry's (GSW) path and absorbs the contact.
Oubre Jr. (GSW) and McDermott (IND) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in Oubre Jr.'s (GSW) path and absorbs the contact.

Oubre Jr. (GSW) veers sideways and initiates contact with Sabonis' (IND) lower half that affects Sabonis' SQBR during the inbound. The contact subsequently causes any further contact Sabonis makes with Oubre Jr.'s head.
Turner (IND) commits a take foul on Green (GSW).
